#Study 
AWS CLI

- AWS cli used to push the docker images on ECR
- AWS cli installation ref doc
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/getting-started-install.html

- command to check AWS cli is working 
   AWS --version
- IAM -> user -> create new user -> check programmatic access -> set permission [ AmazonElasticContainerRegisteryPublicFullAccess ] [ for private repo : AmazonElasticContainerRegisteryPublicFullAccess ] -> create user submit -> will get access key Id and secret access key

- To configure AWS cli cmd :
AWS configure 
- Will ask below details:
          - AWS access key id
          - secret access key
          - default region name
          - default output format : json
 - we can view this details in file ./AWS/credentials

Format of the credentials file 
[default]
aws_access_key_id=123
aws_secret_access_key=abcd

- similar default profile we can add multiple profile in same file 

[dev]
aws_access_key_id=123
aws_secret_access_key=abc
-------------------------------------
